<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>&quot;First off, I hate KEI. Its done more to imbalance the game than any other single factor I can think of.&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>&quot;But I always found the idea of chanters charging 100pp for a buff offensively greedy.&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Seem to contradict himself?  You betcha.  100pp sounds like one hell of a bargain to be able to take advantage of the most imbalancing factor in the game.<br>
<br>
Second, I'd like to note that atleast half the posts in the thread are useless.  For some reason, when someone mentions KEI, it never fails to have a whole legion of posts like<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>&quot;I don't get KEI much but if I do I pay well&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>&quot;I usually pay 20-30pp and give a port&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
and such forth.  I don't think there's anyone who cares about your personal donations, so you can stop posting now.  That's not what the thread is about.<br>
<br>
Third, it is very easy to handle KEI requests.  Don't.  Garbhad has got this one down perfectly (it seems), and I know I do.  It doesn't matter if you are anon or not, just don't respond to people.  If someone says 'hi' to me and I don't know them, I can assume it's a KEI tell and I ignore them.  If it wasn't about KEI, well they shouldn't have made small talk anyway.<br>
<br>
Fourth, if someone pesters and your ignore list is full, there's a plethora of answers you can provide (although ignoring is by far the best).  &quot;Kei leads to the deprivation of enchanters in groups&quot; is a good one.  &quot;I don't cast KEI on anyone&quot; works.  &quot;You are not in my guild, I don't care about you&quot; is fun too.  &quot;I feel no desire to KEI you.&quot;  &quot;You are not in my group and I wouldn't invite you anyway.&quot;  So on and so on.  I would refrain from telling someone to &quot;f.uck off&quot; as they can /report you for offending them if you send that as a direct response.  However, having &quot;f.uck off&quot; as an afk message is totally open game.<br>
<br>
Fifth, I used to have problems with the simply unreal frequency at which I would get KEI requests.  That changed when I adopted the practices that I now teach.  After telling people to f.uck off time and time again, and in general harassing anyone who so much as bothers me, I guess I've developed a reputation as someone you simply don't ask for KEI.  That bodes extremely well for me.<br>
<br>
Sixth, a price floor on KEI would not work, as there is no one to enforce your proposed restrictions and your price would be undercut time and time again.<br>
<br>
Seven, Griftin is a sack of crap and I laugh in his general direction.<br>
<br>
Eight, if all these guidelines were followed by more enchanters, the price of KEI would go up and the requests would go way down.  Enchanters would also get in groups much more often, as they now would have something extra to provide to the group.<br>
<br>
Ninth, you don't have to cave into your guildmates either.  If random guilded SK wants to solo but needs KEI, you can tell him to kill while your gimp ass is invis in a corner leeching exp.  There's only four people in Everquest I will KEI without exception (3 being guildies) and it works out very well for me.  It sucks telling guild members no, but if you don't set a precedent, you will be bothered time and time again.<br>
<br>
And finally, tenth, if you have any problem with my guidelines, just remember that I am not the one posting complaints on the tavern.  I've solved my problems with KEI, and so can anyone else.  It's not the job of the server to stop harassing the enchanter, it's the job of the enchanter to stop being a pussy. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=205399">Yes, my hat looks like crap.</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nandarie>Nandarie</A> at: 4/16/03 3:22:05 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hildie>Hildie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:green;'>Tavern Patron</span></span><br>  Posts: 123<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(4/16/03 4:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3209.topic&index=66>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kei</span><hr size=1> If being a pussy means I don't want to be completely selfish in my playing of the game, then I suppose I am.<br>
